 <span class=usertitle>/cons RED</span><br>  Posts: 394<br> <font color=#FF0000>(11/20/02 6:01 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.steelwarrior.org/forum/p_rip.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: Sacrificial Remains in Ak</span><hr size=1> I took a coth mage with me and parked him at zone in.  Then I ran down and cleared all the worm traps, got coth'd.  Let them despawn.  Invis'd myself and ran back down.  Then killed the back 3 remains repeatedly until the shimmering precense spawned.  Did my turn in etc.  I aggro'd up top a couple times, but just had mage coth me.  Not real easy to get a mage to sit there with you for 30-90 minutes tho, but you can always offer to pay him heh.  FD classes can do this trivially solo. <p><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.hiddencircle.org/view_profile.php?num=1">Gurgel Troll Warlord</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--><br>
<!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.hiddencircle.org/view_profile.php?num=78">Splack Dwarf High Priest</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/bthesteelwarrior.showUserPublicProfile?gid=maultar>Maultar</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are superior</span><br>  Posts: 66<br> <font color=#FF0000>(11/21/02 6:31 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.steelwarrior.org/forum/p_rip.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: Sacrificial Remains in Ak</span><hr size=1> Interesting tactic.  Thanks.  I had a chance to go there last night with a group or more.  Was about 7 of us that needed :P Needless to say I didn't get or stick around too long.  Will try later. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/bthesteelwarrior.showUserPublicProfile?gid=aauminki>Aauminki</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_fire.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>will kick your @$$</span><br>  Posts: 1245<br> <font color=#FF0000>(11/21/02 6:57 am)</font><br>     <br>ezSupporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.steelwarrior.org/forum/p_rip.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: Sacrificial Remains in Ak</span><hr size=1> Save yourself a lot of time and spawn/train the traps (or get CoH) before you move in, there's a very high probability that nothing on the way sees invis (tho the wailing/chanting shades may). If you have a group, just keep the top 4-arms dead they are really easy and spawn as fast as the remains, just make absolutely 100% sure that you SNARE them, explain to your snarer that snaring before they run is critical. <p><big><center><b><a href=http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=19405 target=blank>Marshall Sscaley Iceblade</a><br><i><a href=http://companions.windsofstorm.net>The Companions ~ Team Headstart</a></i> <br>
